   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Their Land Being Full of Idols</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Their land was full of idols; they bowed down to the work of their hands, to that which their fingers had made v. 8 . They were rich not only in money but also in idols.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Idols always go together with money.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>This is true of worldly people today.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>When such people are rich in money, they are also rich in idols.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>This is why money is called mammon Matt 6:24; Luke 16:9, 11, 13 .</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Because the nations trusted in their idols, God judged them in order to humiliate them.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Thus, the ordinary man was humbled, and the man of distinction was abased Isa 2:9a .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Asking Jehovah Not to Forgive Them</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In his accusation against the haughty nations, Isaiah asked Jehovah not to forgive them v. 9b .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>B. Jehovah's Humiliating Judgment</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In 2:10-22 we see Jehovah's humiliating judgment on the haughty nations.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The Object of Jehovah's Humiliating Judgment a. Man's Haughty Look and Man's Loftiness</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The first object of God's judgment is man's haughty look and man's loftiness vv.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>11a, 17a .</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Each person has his own kind of look.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>For example, a banker has a banker's look, and a professor has a professor's look.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Those with a haughty look make a display of their dignity.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The same is true of those who are lofty.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>b.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Everything Proud and Lofty and Everything Lifted Up</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>God judges whatever is lofty and proud and whatever is lifted up v. 12 . If we study history, we will see that throughout the ages God has judged those who are proud, lofty, and lifted up.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>c.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>All the Lofty and Lifted-up Cedars</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>of Lebanon and All the Oaks of Bashan</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The objects of Jehovah's judgment also include all the lofty and lifted-up cedars of Lebanon and all the oaks of Bashan v. 13 . These cedars and oaks are types of lofty persons, those who lift themselves up.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>All those who uplift themselves and become lofty will be "chopped" through God's judgment.</S>
   </TEXT>
